{
  "name": ".EOD-2: System Refresh",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Asana EOD reconciliation, organ cascade, recurring task checks, Karpathy experiments, git sync. Ordered: critical work first, experiments last.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run EOD-2: System Refresh.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-system-refresh.md.\n\nPhases are ordered by criticality — execute in order, do not skip ahead:\n1. Asana reconciliation (daily reset, carry-forward, recurring task check, blocker registry)\n2. Portfolio + ABPS AI reconciliation\n3. Organ cascade + maintenance + intake processing\n4. Recurring task state checks\n5. Housekeeping (git push, self-audit, changelog)\n6. Experiments (delegate to Karpathy subagent — last, expendable if context is heavy)\n\nAll Asana writes follow the Guardrail Protocol in asana-command-center.md. Protocol: heart.md for experiments."
  }
}
